# CrabBridge Project Guidelines

## Code Style
- **Naming**:
  - Types (structs/enums): `PascalCase`
  - Functions/variables: `snake_case`
  - Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
- **Formatting**: must pass `cargo fmt`
- **Clippy**: must pass `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings`

## Error Handling
- Use `anyhow::Result` or the custom `BridgeError` type
- **Never** use `unwrap()` or `expect()` (except in tests)
- Use the `?` operator for error propagation

## Modularity
- Keep functions single-purpose; aim for no more than 100 lines per function
- Workspace crates: `crabbridge-core` (shared types/config/provider), `crabbridge-server` (HTTP bridge), `crabbridge-desktop` (tray app + setup)
- Keep module responsibilities clear: `handlers.rs` handles HTTP routes only, `opts.rs` handles command-line parsing only, `translate.rs` handles protocol conversion only

## Output Requirements
- ✅ Output complete file contents
- ✅ Include all necessary `use` statements
- ✅ Provide full function body implementations
- ❌ Never use "// ... existing code ..." placeholders
- ❌ Never truncate files

## Security
- Pass API keys via environment variables; never hardcode them
- Use `serde` for safe deserialization
